result.execSummary:
All charges against Na'kiah Jeanette Douglas in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Na'kiah Jeanette Douglas is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:28 PM Prosecuting attorney Chad C La Lor in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Na'kiah Jeanette Douglas in court. Court calls case. Court reviews charges alleged with the defendant. Defendant advised of right to consult an attorney. Defendant acknowledges receipt of the complaint, waives a formal reading and enters a pleas of not guilty on misdemeanor charges. State requests $500 cash bail with conditions of no contact with Centerfolds or victim 2. No use or possession of a dangerous weapon. Notes that the case was initially filed as a misdemeanor and was refiled as a felony. Was on a signature bond in the misdemeanor file, however, the state was unaware of MN charges at the time of asking for signature bond. State recites prior criminal history and FTAs. State indicates that cash bond is necessary to assure appearance. Defendant indicates that the FTAs were due to mailing issue with the notices. Defendant indicates that she does not qualify with public defender and cannot post $500 cash bail. 
Court notes that the defendant has previously appeared on signature bond and makes voluntary appearance today. Court orders $3,000 signature bond with conditions of No contact with Centerfolds, Victim 1, and Victim 2. No use or possession of a dangerous weapon.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 8, 2022 at 09:45 am.
Status conference scheduled for June 6, 2022 at 03:00 pm.
